The paper discusses the use of Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) for sequence generation and control, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Specifically, the paper focuses on the use of Long Short Term Memory (LSTM) RNNs, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) and text generation tasks, indicating a potential fit for the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of a gestural interface for user control, suggesting a potential fit for the cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) sub-category. Overall, the paper's focus on RNNs, NLP, and interactive control suggest likely sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
